==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Whom
<hw>Whom</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>pron.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>wham</ets>,
AS. dative <ets>hw⟦amac⟧m</ets>, <ets>hw<?/m</ets>. See
<er>Who</er>.]</ety> <def>The objective case of <xex>who</xex>. See
<er>Who</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ In Old English, <xex>whom</xex> was also commonly used
as a dative. Cf. <er>Him</er>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And every grass that groweth upon root⟦br⟧
She shall eke know, and <qex>whom</qex> it will do boot.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whomsoever</ent>⟦br⟧
